# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the
# CVE/advisory description only.
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# CVE-2026-58277 | Microsoft SharePoint | Broken Access Control / Privilege Escalation
# CVSS: 8.8 (HIGH) [1] | is_kev: false | Priority Tier: STANDARD
#
# Detection rationale:
# This vulnerability involves improper authorization in SharePoint,
# allowing an already-authenticated attacker to escalate privileges via
# network-accessible HTTP endpoints [2]. SharePoint REST and SOAP API
# endpoints (e.g., /_api/, /_vti_bin/, /_layouts/) are the typical
# attack surface for authorization-bypass class vulnerabilities on this
# platform. Without PCAP data or a public PoC, the pattern below targets
# anomalous access to SharePoint privilege-sensitive API paths combined
# with HTTP methods (POST/PUT) that could be used to modify permissions
# or role assignments. This is a BEST-EFFORT heuristic and will require
# analyst tuning to reduce false positives in environments with normal
# SharePoint administrative activity.
#
# NOTE: The Microsoft advisory page [2] was partially rendered at
# collection time (JavaScript-dependent content). No granular technical
# detail (specific endpoint, request parameter, or payload pattern) was
# extractable from it. This rule is therefore LOW CONFIDENCE and MUST
# be reviewed and validated by a SharePoint-familiar analyst before
# any deployment.
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTE: Only a single CVSS score of 8.8 (HIGH) is
# present in the provided context [1][2][3]. No discrepancy between
# sources was detected; however, analysts should verify NVD [1] and
# Microsoft MSRC [2] independently in case scores diverge as the record
# matures (the CVE is 5 days old).
#
# This rule is a proposed draft for analyst review.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-58277 Microsoft SharePoint broken access control privilege escalation attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"POST";
  http.uri; content:"/_api/"; nocase;
  pcre:"/\/_api\/(web|site|sitegroups|roleassignments|roledefinitions|lists|permissions)/i";
  reference:cve,2026-58277;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1548, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin; sid:9000044; rev:1; )

